President Obama announced his intent to recess appoint four nominees to key administration posts that have been left vacant for an extended period of time. The President urged members of the Senate to stop playing politics with the nominees and fulfill their responsibilities of advice and consent. The nominees are Maria del Carmen Aponte for Chief of Mission, Republic of El Salvador; Elisabeth Hagen for Under Secretary for Food Safety, Department of Agriculture; Winslow Sargeant for Chief Counsel of Advocacy, Small Business Administration; and Richard Sorian for Assistant Secretary for Public Affairs, Department of Health and Human Services. Each nominee has a background and experience relevant to their respective positions.